    <note>Xing(1) Shicai [3372] Lu Zuqian, WJ, 8.188-9. According to Lu Zuqian, the Xing were originally a Qing(a) zhou lineage, who moved to Bian (ancient name for Kaifeng). I am assuming that this is the same address as that of his collaterial ancestor, Xing(1) Shu [7106]. His zi was Bangyong and his elder brother was Bangjie [14760] in the sacrificial prayer of Lu Zuqian and I therefore assume that the father-in-law #1 of Pan(1) Jingxian [3690], Xing Bangzhi [14759], is another brother (probably referred to by his zi). Shicai was buried in Shanyin xian, but is listed in Zhejiang TZ, 125.29b, as a Shangyu resident jinshi in 1166, which I conclude to be the new residence of his father, Zuo [14758] (who has the same generational name as the younger sons of Xing(1) Shu), who I identify as the lineage uncle of Chun [3371], who has the same generational name as Yi [14763], son of Jiang [14762], who is a younger son of Xing Shu. I should guess that Xing Wenyu, Pan Jingxian's son-in-law, is a grandson of Xing Bangzhi, but I have not included him for lack of any kind of evidence. CBD, 2, 1073.</note>
